 403_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX = {token_type: i for i, token_type in enumerate(_ALL_TOKEN_TYPES)}

 406class Token:
 407    __slots__ = ("token_type", "text", "line", "col", "start", "end", "comments")
 408
 409    @classmethod
 410    def number(cls, number: int) -> Token:
 411        """Returns a NUMBER token with `number` as its text."""
 412        return cls(TokenType.NUMBER, str(number))
 413
 414    @classmethod
 415    def string(cls, string: str) -> Token:
 416        """Returns a STRING token with `string` as its text."""
 417        return cls(TokenType.STRING, string)
 418
 419    @classmethod
 420    def identifier(cls, identifier: str) -> Token:
 421        """Returns an IDENTIFIER token with `identifier` as its text."""
 422        return cls(TokenType.IDENTIFIER, identifier)
 423
 424    @classmethod
 425    def var(cls, var: str) -> Token:
 426        """Returns an VAR token with `var` as its text."""
 427        return cls(TokenType.VAR, var)
 428
 429    def __init__(
 430        self,
 431        token_type: TokenType,
 432        text: str,
 433        line: int = 1,
 434        col: int = 1,
 435        start: int = 0,
 436        end: int = 0,
 437        comments: t.Optional[t.List[str]] = None,
 438    ) -> None:
 439        """Token initializer.
 440
 441        Args:
 442            token_type: The TokenType Enum.
 443            text: The text of the token.
 444            line: The line that the token ends on.
 445            col: The column that the token ends on.
 446            start: The start index of the token.
 447            end: The ending index of the token.
 448            comments: The comments to attach to the token.
 449        """
 450        self.token_type = token_type
 451        self.text = text
 452        self.line = line
 453        self.col = col
 454        self.start = start
 455        self.end = end
 456        self.comments = [] if comments is None else comments
 457
 458    def __repr__(self) -> str:
 459        attributes = ", ".join(f"{k}: {getattr(self, k)}" for k in self.__slots__)
 460        return f"<Token {attributes}>"
 461
 462
 463class _Tokenizer(type):
 464    def __new__(cls, clsname, bases, attrs):
 465        klass = super().__new__(cls, clsname, bases, attrs)
 466
 467        def _convert_quotes(arr: t.List[str | t.Tuple[str, str]]) -> t.Dict[str, str]:
 468            return dict(
 469                (item, item) if isinstance(item, str) else (item[0], item[1]) for item in arr
 470            )
 471
 472        def _quotes_to_format(
 473            token_type: TokenType, arr: t.List[str | t.Tuple[str, str]]
 474        ) -> t.Dict[str, t.Tuple[str, TokenType]]:
 475            return {k: (v, token_type) for k, v in _convert_quotes(arr).items()}
 476
 477        klass._QUOTES = _convert_quotes(klass.QUOTES)
 478        klass._IDENTIFIERS = _convert_quotes(klass.IDENTIFIERS)
 479
 480        klass._FORMAT_STRINGS = {
 481            **{
 482                p + s: (e, TokenType.NATIONAL_STRING)
 483                for s, e in klass._QUOTES.items()
 484                for p in ("n", "N")
 485            },
 486            **_quotes_to_format(TokenType.BIT_STRING, klass.BIT_STRINGS),
 487            **_quotes_to_format(TokenType.BYTE_STRING, klass.BYTE_STRINGS),
 488            **_quotes_to_format(TokenType.HEX_STRING, klass.HEX_STRINGS),
 489            **_quotes_to_format(TokenType.RAW_STRING, klass.RAW_STRINGS),
 490            **_quotes_to_format(TokenType.HEREDOC_STRING, klass.HEREDOC_STRINGS),
 491            **_quotes_to_format(TokenType.UNICODE_STRING, klass.UNICODE_STRINGS),
 492        }
 493
 494        klass._STRING_ESCAPES = set(klass.STRING_ESCAPES)
 495        klass._IDENTIFIER_ESCAPES = set(klass.IDENTIFIER_ESCAPES)
 496        klass._COMMENTS = {
 497            **dict(
 498                (comment, None) if isinstance(comment, str) else (comment[0], comment[1])
 499                for comment in klass.COMMENTS
 500            ),
 501            "{#": "#}",  # Ensure Jinja comments are tokenized correctly in all dialects
 502        }
 503
 504        klass._KEYWORD_TRIE = new_trie(
 505            key.upper()
 506            for key in (
 507                *klass.KEYWORDS,
 508                *klass._COMMENTS,
 509                *klass._QUOTES,
 510                *klass._FORMAT_STRINGS,
 511            )
 512            if " " in key or any(single in key for single in klass.SINGLE_TOKENS)
 513        )
 514
 515        if USE_RS_TOKENIZER:
 516            settings = RsTokenizerSettings(
 517                white_space={k: _TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[v] for k, v in klass.WHITE_SPACE.items()},
 518                single_tokens={k: _TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[v] for k, v in klass.SINGLE_TOKENS.items()},
 519                keywords={k: _TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[v] for k, v in klass.KEYWORDS.items()},
 520                numeric_literals=klass.NUMERIC_LITERALS,
 521                identifiers=klass._IDENTIFIERS,
 522                identifier_escapes=klass._IDENTIFIER_ESCAPES,
 523                string_escapes=klass._STRING_ESCAPES,
 524                quotes=klass._QUOTES,
 525                format_strings={
 526                    k: (v1, _TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[v2])
 527                    for k, (v1, v2) in klass._FORMAT_STRINGS.items()
 528                },
 529                has_bit_strings=bool(klass.BIT_STRINGS),
 530                has_hex_strings=bool(klass.HEX_STRINGS),
 531                comments=klass._COMMENTS,
 532                var_single_tokens=klass.VAR_SINGLE_TOKENS,
 533                commands={_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[v] for v in klass.COMMANDS},
 534                command_prefix_tokens={
 535                    _TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[v] for v in klass.COMMAND_PREFIX_TOKENS
 536                },
 537                heredoc_tag_is_identifier=klass.HEREDOC_TAG_IS_IDENTIFIER,
 538                string_escapes_allowed_in_raw_strings=klass.STRING_ESCAPES_ALLOWED_IN_RAW_STRINGS,
 539                nested_comments=klass.NESTED_COMMENTS,
 540            )
 541            token_types = RsTokenTypeSettings(
 542                bit_string=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.BIT_STRING],
 543                break_=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.BREAK],
 544                dcolon=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.DCOLON],
 545                heredoc_string=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.HEREDOC_STRING],
 546                raw_string=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.RAW_STRING],
 547                hex_string=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.HEX_STRING],
 548                identifier=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.IDENTIFIER],
 549                number=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.NUMBER],
 550                parameter=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.PARAMETER],
 551                semicolon=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.SEMICOLON],
 552                string=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.STRING],
 553                var=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[TokenType.VAR],
 554                heredoc_string_alternative=_TOKEN_TYPE_TO_INDEX[klass.HEREDOC_STRING_ALTERNATIVE],
 555            )
 556            klass._RS_TOKENIZER = RsTokenizer(settings, token_types)
 557        else:
 558            klass._RS_TOKENIZER = None
 559
 560        return klass

 962    def __init__(self, dialect: DialectType = None) -> None:
 963        from sqlglot.dialects import Dialect
 964
 965        self.dialect = Dialect.get_or_raise(dialect)
 966
 967        if USE_RS_TOKENIZER:
 968            self._rs_dialect_settings = RsTokenizerDialectSettings(
 969                unescaped_sequences=self.dialect.UNESCAPED_SEQUENCES,
 970                identifiers_can_start_with_digit=self.dialect.IDENTIFIERS_CAN_START_WITH_DIGIT,
 971            )
 972
 973        self.reset()

 975    def reset(self) -> None:
 976        self.sql = ""
 977        self.size = 0
 978        self.tokens: t.List[Token] = []
 979        self._start = 0
 980        self._current = 0
 981        self._line = 1
 982        self._col = 0
 983        self._comments: t.List[str] = []
 984
 985        self._char = ""
 986        self._end = False
 987        self._peek = ""
 988        self._prev_token_line = -1
 989
 990    def tokenize(self, sql: str) -> t.List[Token]:
 991        """Returns a list of tokens corresponding to the SQL string `sql`."""
 992        if USE_RS_TOKENIZER:
 993            return self.tokenize_rs(sql)
 994
 995        self.reset()
 996        self.sql = sql
 997        self.size = len(sql)
 998
 999        try:
1000            self._scan()
1001        except Exception as e:
1002            start = max(self._current - 50, 0)
1003            end = min(self._current + 50, self.size - 1)
1004            context = self.sql[start:end]
1005            raise TokenError(f"Error tokenizing '{context}'") from e
1006
1007        return self.tokens
1008
1009    def _scan(self, until: t.Optional[t.Callable] = None) -> None:
1010        while self.size and not self._end:
1011            current = self._current
1012
1013            # Skip spaces here rather than iteratively calling advance() for performance reasons
1014            while current < self.size:
1015                char = self.sql[current]
1016
1017                if char.isspace() and (char == " " or char == "\t"):
1018                    current += 1
1019                else:
1020                    break
1021
1022            offset = current - self._current if current > self._current else 1
1023
1024            self._start = current
1025            self._advance(offset)
1026
1027            if not self._char.isspace():
1028                if self._char.isdigit():
1029                    self._scan_number()
1030                elif self._char in self._IDENTIFIERS:
1031                    self._scan_identifier(self._IDENTIFIERS[self._char])
1032                else:
1033                    self._scan_keywords()
1034
1035            if until and until():
1036                break
1037
1038        if self.tokens and self._comments:
1039            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
1040
1041    def _chars(self, size: int) -> str:
1042        if size == 1:
1043            return self._char
1044
1045        start = self._current - 1
1046        end = start + size
1047
1048        return self.sql[start:end] if end <= self.size else ""
1049
1050    def _advance(self, i: int = 1, alnum: bool = False) -> None:
1051        if self.WHITE_SPACE.get(self._char) is TokenType.BREAK:
1052            # Ensures we don't count an extra line if we get a \r\n line break sequence
1053            if not (self._char == "\r" and self._peek == "\n"):
1054                self._col = 1
1055                self._line += 1
1056        else:
1057            self._col += i
1058
1059        self._current += i
1060        self._end = self._current >= self.size
1061        self._char = self.sql[self._current - 1]
1062        self._peek = "" if self._end else self.sql[self._current]
1063
1064        if alnum and self._char.isalnum():
1065            # Here we use local variables instead of attributes for better performance
1066            _col = self._col
1067            _current = self._current
1068            _end = self._end
1069            _peek = self._peek
1070
1071            while _peek.isalnum():
1072                _col += 1
1073                _current += 1
1074                _end = _current >= self.size
1075                _peek = "" if _end else self.sql[_current]
1076
1077            self._col = _col
1078            self._current = _current
1079            self._end = _end
1080            self._peek = _peek
1081            self._char = self.sql[_current - 1]
1082
1083    @property
1084    def _text(self) -> str:
1085        return self.sql[self._start : self._current]
1086
1087    def _add(self, token_type: TokenType, text: t.Optional[str] = None) -> None:
1088        self._prev_token_line = self._line
1089
1090        if self._comments and token_type == TokenType.SEMICOLON and self.tokens:
1091            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
1092            self._comments = []
1093
1094        self.tokens.append(
1095            Token(
1096                token_type,
1097                text=self._text if text is None else text,
1098                line=self._line,
1099                col=self._col,
1100                start=self._start,
1101                end=self._current - 1,
1102                comments=self._comments,
1103            )
1104        )
1105        self._comments = []
1106
1107        # If we have either a semicolon or a begin token before the command's token, we'll parse
1108        # whatever follows the command's token as a string
1109        if (
1110            token_type in self.COMMANDS
1111            and self._peek != ";"
1112            and (len(self.tokens) == 1 or self.tokens[-2].token_type in self.COMMAND_PREFIX_TOKENS)
1113        ):
1114            start = self._current
1115            tokens = len(self.tokens)
1116            self._scan(lambda: self._peek == ";")
1117            self.tokens = self.tokens[:tokens]
1118            text = self.sql[start : self._current].strip()
1119            if text:
1120                self._add(TokenType.STRING, text)
1121
1122    def _scan_keywords(self) -> None:
1123        size = 0
1124        word = None
1125        chars = self._text
1126        char = chars
1127        prev_space = False
1128        skip = False
1129        trie = self._KEYWORD_TRIE
1130        single_token = char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS
1131
1132        while chars:
1133            if skip:
1134                result = TrieResult.PREFIX
1135            else:
1136                result, trie = in_trie(trie, char.upper())
1137
1138            if result == TrieResult.FAILED:
1139                break
1140            if result == TrieResult.EXISTS:
1141                word = chars
1142
1143            end = self._current + size
1144            size += 1
1145
1146            if end < self.size:
1147                char = self.sql[end]
1148                single_token = single_token or char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS
1149                is_space = char.isspace()
1150
1151                if not is_space or not prev_space:
1152                    if is_space:
1153                        char = " "
1154                    chars += char
1155                    prev_space = is_space
1156                    skip = False
1157                else:
1158                    skip = True
1159            else:
1160                char = ""
1161                break
1162
1163        if word:
1164            if self._scan_string(word):
1165                return
1166            if self._scan_comment(word):
1167                return
1168            if prev_space or single_token or not char:
1169                self._advance(size - 1)
1170                word = word.upper()
1171                self._add(self.KEYWORDS[word], text=word)
1172                return
1173
1174        if self._char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1175            self._add(self.SINGLE_TOKENS[self._char], text=self._char)
1176            return
1177
1178        self._scan_var()
1179
1180    def _scan_comment(self, comment_start: str) -> bool:
1181        if comment_start not in self._COMMENTS:
1182            return False
1183
1184        comment_start_line = self._line
1185        comment_start_size = len(comment_start)
1186        comment_end = self._COMMENTS[comment_start]
1187
1188        if comment_end:
1189            # Skip the comment's start delimiter
1190            self._advance(comment_start_size)
1191
1192            comment_count = 1
1193            comment_end_size = len(comment_end)
1194
1195            while not self._end:
1196                if self._chars(comment_end_size) == comment_end:
1197                    comment_count -= 1
1198                    if not comment_count:
1199                        break
1200
1201                self._advance(alnum=True)
1202
1203                # Nested comments are allowed by some dialects, e.g. databricks, duckdb, postgres
1204                if (
1205                    self.NESTED_COMMENTS
1206                    and not self._end
1207                    and self._chars(comment_end_size) == comment_start
1208                ):
1209                    self._advance(comment_start_size)
1210                    comment_count += 1
1211
1212            self._comments.append(self._text[comment_start_size : -comment_end_size + 1])
1213            self._advance(comment_end_size - 1)
1214        else:
1215            while not self._end and self.WHITE_SPACE.get(self._peek) is not TokenType.BREAK:
1216                self._advance(alnum=True)
1217            self._comments.append(self._text[comment_start_size:])
1218
1219        # Leading comment is attached to the succeeding token, whilst trailing comment to the preceding.
1220        # Multiple consecutive comments are preserved by appending them to the current comments list.
1221        if comment_start_line == self._prev_token_line:
1222            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
1223            self._comments = []
1224            self._prev_token_line = self._line
1225
1226        return True
1227
1228    def _scan_number(self) -> None:
1229        if self._char == "0":
1230            peek = self._peek.upper()
1231            if peek == "B":
1232                return self._scan_bits() if self.BIT_STRINGS else self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1233            elif peek == "X":
1234                return self._scan_hex() if self.HEX_STRINGS else self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1235
1236        decimal = False
1237        scientific = 0
1238
1239        while True:
1240            if self._peek.isdigit():
1241                self._advance()
1242            elif self._peek == "." and not decimal:
1243                if self.tokens and self.tokens[-1].token_type == TokenType.PARAMETER:
1244                    return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1245                decimal = True
1246                self._advance()
1247            elif self._peek in ("-", "+") and scientific == 1:
1248                scientific += 1
1249                self._advance()
1250            elif self._peek.upper() == "E" and not scientific:
1251                scientific += 1
1252                self._advance()
1253            elif self._peek.isidentifier():
1254                number_text = self._text
1255                literal = ""
1256
1257                while self._peek.strip() and self._peek not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1258                    literal += self._peek
1259                    self._advance()
1260
1261                token_type = self.KEYWORDS.get(self.NUMERIC_LITERALS.get(literal.upper(), ""))
1262
1263                if token_type:
1264                    self._add(TokenType.NUMBER, number_text)
1265                    self._add(TokenType.DCOLON, "::")
1266                    return self._add(token_type, literal)
1267                elif self.dialect.IDENTIFIERS_CAN_START_WITH_DIGIT:
1268                    return self._add(TokenType.VAR)
1269
1270                self._advance(-len(literal))
1271                return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER, number_text)
1272            else:
1273                return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1274
1275    def _scan_bits(self) -> None:
1276        self._advance()
1277        value = self._extract_value()
1278        try:
1279            # If `value` can't be converted to a binary, fallback to tokenizing it as an identifier
1280            int(value, 2)
1281            self._add(TokenType.BIT_STRING, value[2:])  # Drop the 0b
1282        except ValueError:
1283            self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER)
1284
1285    def _scan_hex(self) -> None:
1286        self._advance()
1287        value = self._extract_value()
1288        try:
1289            # If `value` can't be converted to a hex, fallback to tokenizing it as an identifier
1290            int(value, 16)
1291            self._add(TokenType.HEX_STRING, value[2:])  # Drop the 0x
1292        except ValueError:
1293            self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER)
1294
1295    def _extract_value(self) -> str:
1296        while True:
1297            char = self._peek.strip()
1298            if char and char not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1299                self._advance(alnum=True)
1300            else:
1301                break
1302
1303        return self._text
1304
1305    def _scan_string(self, start: str) -> bool:
1306        base = None
1307        token_type = TokenType.STRING
1308
1309        if start in self._QUOTES:
1310            end = self._QUOTES[start]
1311        elif start in self._FORMAT_STRINGS:
1312            end, token_type = self._FORMAT_STRINGS[start]
1313
1314            if token_type == TokenType.HEX_STRING:
1315                base = 16
1316            elif token_type == TokenType.BIT_STRING:
1317                base = 2
1318            elif token_type == TokenType.HEREDOC_STRING:
1319                self._advance()
1320
1321                if self._char == end:
1322                    tag = ""
1323                else:
1324                    tag = self._extract_string(
1325                        end,
1326                        raw_string=True,
1327                        raise_unmatched=not self.HEREDOC_TAG_IS_IDENTIFIER,
1328                    )
1329
1330                if tag and self.HEREDOC_TAG_IS_IDENTIFIER and (self._end or not tag.isidentifier()):
1331                    if not self._end:
1332                        self._advance(-1)
1333
1334                    self._advance(-len(tag))
1335                    self._add(self.HEREDOC_STRING_ALTERNATIVE)
1336                    return True
1337
1338                end = f"{start}{tag}{end}"
1339        else:
1340            return False
1341
1342        self._advance(len(start))
1343        text = self._extract_string(end, raw_string=token_type == TokenType.RAW_STRING)
1344
1345        if base:
1346            try:
1347                int(text, base)
1348            except Exception:
1349                raise TokenError(
1350                    f"Numeric string contains invalid characters from {self._line}:{self._start}"
1351                )
1352
1353        self._add(token_type, text)
1354        return True
1355
1356    def _scan_identifier(self, identifier_end: str) -> None:
1357        self._advance()
1358        text = self._extract_string(identifier_end, escapes=self._IDENTIFIER_ESCAPES)
1359        self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER, text)
1360
1361    def _scan_var(self) -> None:
1362        while True:
1363            char = self._peek.strip()
1364            if char and (char in self.VAR_SINGLE_TOKENS or char not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS):
1365                self._advance(alnum=True)
1366            else:
1367                break
1368
1369        self._add(
1370            TokenType.VAR
1371            if self.tokens and self.tokens[-1].token_type == TokenType.PARAMETER
1372            else self.KEYWORDS.get(self._text.upper(), TokenType.VAR)
1373        )
1374
1375    def _extract_string(
1376        self,
1377        delimiter: str,
1378        escapes: t.Optional[t.Set[str]] = None,
1379        raw_string: bool = False,
1380        raise_unmatched: bool = True,
1381    ) -> str:
1382        text = ""
1383        delim_size = len(delimiter)
1384        escapes = self._STRING_ESCAPES if escapes is None else escapes
1385
1386        while True:
1387            if (
1388                not raw_string
1389                and self.dialect.UNESCAPED_SEQUENCES
1390                and self._peek
1391                and self._char in self.STRING_ESCAPES
1392            ):
1393                unescaped_sequence = self.dialect.UNESCAPED_SEQUENCES.get(self._char + self._peek)
1394                if unescaped_sequence:
1395                    self._advance(2)
1396                    text += unescaped_sequence
1397                    continue
1398            if (
1399                (self.STRING_ESCAPES_ALLOWED_IN_RAW_STRINGS or not raw_string)
1400                and self._char in escapes
1401                and (self._peek == delimiter or self._peek in escapes)
1402                and (self._char not in self._QUOTES or self._char == self._peek)
1403            ):
1404                if self._peek == delimiter:
1405                    text += self._peek
1406                else:
1407                    text += self._char + self._peek
1408
1409                if self._current + 1 < self.size:
1410                    self._advance(2)
1411                else:
1412                    raise TokenError(f"Missing {delimiter} from {self._line}:{self._current}")
1413            else:
1414                if self._chars(delim_size) == delimiter:
1415                    if delim_size > 1:
1416                        self._advance(delim_size - 1)
1417                    break
1418
1419                if self._end:
1420                    if not raise_unmatched:
1421                        return text + self._char
1422
1423                    raise TokenError(f"Missing {delimiter} from {self._line}:{self._start}")
1424
1425                current = self._current - 1
1426                self._advance(alnum=True)
1427                text += self.sql[current : self._current - 1]
1428
1429        return text
1430
1431    def tokenize_rs(self, sql: str) -> t.List[Token]:
1432        if not self._RS_TOKENIZER:
1433            raise SqlglotError("Rust tokenizer is not available")
1434
1435        try:
1436            tokens = self._RS_TOKENIZER.tokenize(sql, self._rs_dialect_settings)
1437            for token in tokens:
1438                token.token_type = _ALL_TOKEN_TYPES[token.token_type_index]
1439            return tokens
1440        except Exception as e:
1441            raise TokenError(str(e))

  • text: The text of the token.

  • col: The column that the token ends on.

  • end: The ending index of the token.
  • comments: The comments to attach to the token.

 976    def reset(self) -> None:
 977        self.sql = ""
 978        self.size = 0
 979        self.tokens: t.List[Token] = []
 980        self._start = 0
 981        self._current = 0
 982        self._line = 1
 983        self._col = 0
 984        self._comments: t.List[str] = []
 985
 986        self._char = ""
 987        self._end = False
 988        self._peek = ""
 989        self._prev_token_line = -1

 991    def tokenize(self, sql: str) -> t.List[Token]:
 992        """Returns a list of tokens corresponding to the SQL string `sql`."""
 993        if USE_RS_TOKENIZER:
 994            return self.tokenize_rs(sql)
 995
 996        self.reset()
 997        self.sql = sql
 998        self.size = len(sql)
 999
1000        try:
1001            self._scan()
1002        except Exception as e:
1003            start = max(self._current - 50, 0)
1004            end = min(self._current + 50, self.size - 1)
1005            context = self.sql[start:end]
1006            raise TokenError(f"Error tokenizing '{context}'") from e
1007
1008        return self.tokens
1009
1010    def _scan(self, until: t.Optional[t.Callable] = None) -> None:
1011        while self.size and not self._end:
1012            current = self._current
1013
1014            # Skip spaces here rather than iteratively calling advance() for performance reasons
1015            while current < self.size:
1016                char = self.sql[current]
1017
1018                if char.isspace() and (char == " " or char == "\t"):
1019                    current += 1
1020                else:
1021                    break
1022
1023            offset = current - self._current if current > self._current else 1
1024
1025            self._start = current
1026            self._advance(offset)
1027
1028            if not self._char.isspace():
1029                if self._char.isdigit():
1030                    self._scan_number()
1031                elif self._char in self._IDENTIFIERS:
1032                    self._scan_identifier(self._IDENTIFIERS[self._char])
1033                else:
1034                    self._scan_keywords()
1035
1036            if until and until():
1037                break
1038
1039        if self.tokens and self._comments:
1040            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
1041
1042    def _chars(self, size: int) -> str:
1043        if size == 1:
1044            return self._char
1045
1046        start = self._current - 1
1047        end = start + size
1048
1049        return self.sql[start:end] if end <= self.size else ""
1050
1051    def _advance(self, i: int = 1, alnum: bool = False) -> None:
1052        if self.WHITE_SPACE.get(self._char) is TokenType.BREAK:
1053            # Ensures we don't count an extra line if we get a \r\n line break sequence
1054            if not (self._char == "\r" and self._peek == "\n"):
1055                self._col = 1
1056                self._line += 1
1057        else:
1058            self._col += i
1059
1060        self._current += i
1061        self._end = self._current >= self.size
1062        self._char = self.sql[self._current - 1]
1063        self._peek = "" if self._end else self.sql[self._current]
1064
1065        if alnum and self._char.isalnum():
1066            # Here we use local variables instead of attributes for better performance
1067            _col = self._col
1068            _current = self._current
1069            _end = self._end
1070            _peek = self._peek
1071
1072            while _peek.isalnum():
1073                _col += 1
1074                _current += 1
1075                _end = _current >= self.size
1076                _peek = "" if _end else self.sql[_current]
1077
1078            self._col = _col
1079            self._current = _current
1080            self._end = _end
1081            self._peek = _peek
1082            self._char = self.sql[_current - 1]
1083
1084    @property
1085    def _text(self) -> str:
1086        return self.sql[self._start : self._current]
1087
1088    def _add(self, token_type: TokenType, text: t.Optional[str] = None) -> None:
1089        self._prev_token_line = self._line
1090
1091        if self._comments and token_type == TokenType.SEMICOLON and self.tokens:
1092            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
1093            self._comments = []
1094
1095        self.tokens.append(
1096            Token(
1097                token_type,
1098                text=self._text if text is None else text,
1099                line=self._line,
1100                col=self._col,
1101                start=self._start,
1102                end=self._current - 1,
1103                comments=self._comments,
1104            )
1105        )
1106        self._comments = []
1107
1108        # If we have either a semicolon or a begin token before the command's token, we'll parse
1109        # whatever follows the command's token as a string
1110        if (
1111            token_type in self.COMMANDS
1112            and self._peek != ";"
1113            and (len(self.tokens) == 1 or self.tokens[-2].token_type in self.COMMAND_PREFIX_TOKENS)
1114        ):
1115            start = self._current
1116            tokens = len(self.tokens)
1117            self._scan(lambda: self._peek == ";")
1118            self.tokens = self.tokens[:tokens]
1119            text = self.sql[start : self._current].strip()
1120            if text:
1121                self._add(TokenType.STRING, text)

1123    def _scan_keywords(self) -> None:
1124        size = 0
1125        word = None
1126        chars = self._text
1127        char = chars
1128        prev_space = False
1129        skip = False
1130        trie = self._KEYWORD_TRIE
1131        single_token = char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS
1132
1133        while chars:
1134            if skip:
1135                result = TrieResult.PREFIX
1136            else:
1137                result, trie = in_trie(trie, char.upper())
1138
1139            if result == TrieResult.FAILED:
1140                break
1141            if result == TrieResult.EXISTS:
1142                word = chars
1143
1144            end = self._current + size
1145            size += 1
1146
1147            if end < self.size:
1148                char = self.sql[end]
1149                single_token = single_token or char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS
1150                is_space = char.isspace()
1151
1152                if not is_space or not prev_space:
1153                    if is_space:
1154                        char = " "
1155                    chars += char
1156                    prev_space = is_space
1157                    skip = False
1158                else:
1159                    skip = True
1160            else:
1161                char = ""
1162                break
1163
1164        if word:
1165            if self._scan_string(word):
1166                return
1167            if self._scan_comment(word):
1168                return
1169            if prev_space or single_token or not char:
1170                self._advance(size - 1)
1171                word = word.upper()
1172                self._add(self.KEYWORDS[word], text=word)
1173                return
1174
1175        if self._char in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1176            self._add(self.SINGLE_TOKENS[self._char], text=self._char)
1177            return
1178
1179        self._scan_var()

1181    def _scan_comment(self, comment_start: str) -> bool:
1182        if comment_start not in self._COMMENTS:
1183            return False
1184
1185        comment_start_line = self._line
1186        comment_start_size = len(comment_start)
1187        comment_end = self._COMMENTS[comment_start]
1188
1189        if comment_end:
1190            # Skip the comment's start delimiter
1191            self._advance(comment_start_size)
1192
1193            comment_count = 1
1194            comment_end_size = len(comment_end)
1195
1196            while not self._end:
1197                if self._chars(comment_end_size) == comment_end:
1198                    comment_count -= 1
1199                    if not comment_count:
1200                        break
1201
1202                self._advance(alnum=True)
1203
1204                # Nested comments are allowed by some dialects, e.g. databricks, duckdb, postgres
1205                if (
1206                    self.NESTED_COMMENTS
1207                    and not self._end
1208                    and self._chars(comment_end_size) == comment_start
1209                ):
1210                    self._advance(comment_start_size)
1211                    comment_count += 1
1212
1213            self._comments.append(self._text[comment_start_size : -comment_end_size + 1])
1214            self._advance(comment_end_size - 1)
1215        else:
1216            while not self._end and self.WHITE_SPACE.get(self._peek) is not TokenType.BREAK:
1217                self._advance(alnum=True)
1218            self._comments.append(self._text[comment_start_size:])
1219
1220        # Leading comment is attached to the succeeding token, whilst trailing comment to the preceding.
1221        # Multiple consecutive comments are preserved by appending them to the current comments list.
1222        if comment_start_line == self._prev_token_line:
1223            self.tokens[-1].comments.extend(self._comments)
1224            self._comments = []
1225            self._prev_token_line = self._line
1226
1227        return True

1229    def _scan_number(self) -> None:
1230        if self._char == "0":
1231            peek = self._peek.upper()
1232            if peek == "B":
1233                return self._scan_bits() if self.BIT_STRINGS else self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1234            elif peek == "X":
1235                return self._scan_hex() if self.HEX_STRINGS else self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1236
1237        decimal = False
1238        scientific = 0
1239
1240        while True:
1241            if self._peek.isdigit():
1242                self._advance()
1243            elif self._peek == "." and not decimal:
1244                if self.tokens and self.tokens[-1].token_type == TokenType.PARAMETER:
1245                    return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1246                decimal = True
1247                self._advance()
1248            elif self._peek in ("-", "+") and scientific == 1:
1249                scientific += 1
1250                self._advance()
1251            elif self._peek.upper() == "E" and not scientific:
1252                scientific += 1
1253                self._advance()
1254            elif self._peek.isidentifier():
1255                number_text = self._text
1256                literal = ""
1257
1258                while self._peek.strip() and self._peek not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1259                    literal += self._peek
1260                    self._advance()
1261
1262                token_type = self.KEYWORDS.get(self.NUMERIC_LITERALS.get(literal.upper(), ""))
1263
1264                if token_type:
1265                    self._add(TokenType.NUMBER, number_text)
1266                    self._add(TokenType.DCOLON, "::")
1267                    return self._add(token_type, literal)
1268                elif self.dialect.IDENTIFIERS_CAN_START_WITH_DIGIT:
1269                    return self._add(TokenType.VAR)
1270
1271                self._advance(-len(literal))
1272                return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER, number_text)
1273            else:
1274                return self._add(TokenType.NUMBER)
1275
1276    def _scan_bits(self) -> None:
1277        self._advance()
1278        value = self._extract_value()
1279        try:
1280            # If `value` can't be converted to a binary, fallback to tokenizing it as an identifier
1281            int(value, 2)
1282            self._add(TokenType.BIT_STRING, value[2:])  # Drop the 0b
1283        except ValueError:
1284            self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER)
1285
1286    def _scan_hex(self) -> None:
1287        self._advance()
1288        value = self._extract_value()
1289        try:
1290            # If `value` can't be converted to a hex, fallback to tokenizing it as an identifier
1291            int(value, 16)
1292            self._add(TokenType.HEX_STRING, value[2:])  # Drop the 0x
1293        except ValueError:
1294            self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER)

1296    def _extract_value(self) -> str:
1297        while True:
1298            char = self._peek.strip()
1299            if char and char not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS:
1300                self._advance(alnum=True)
1301            else:
1302                break
1303
1304        return self._text

1306    def _scan_string(self, start: str) -> bool:
1307        base = None
1308        token_type = TokenType.STRING
1309
1310        if start in self._QUOTES:
1311            end = self._QUOTES[start]
1312        elif start in self._FORMAT_STRINGS:
1313            end, token_type = self._FORMAT_STRINGS[start]
1314
1315            if token_type == TokenType.HEX_STRING:
1316                base = 16
1317            elif token_type == TokenType.BIT_STRING:
1318                base = 2
1319            elif token_type == TokenType.HEREDOC_STRING:
1320                self._advance()
1321
1322                if self._char == end:
1323                    tag = ""
1324                else:
1325                    tag = self._extract_string(
1326                        end,
1327                        raw_string=True,
1328                        raise_unmatched=not self.HEREDOC_TAG_IS_IDENTIFIER,
1329                    )
1330
1331                if tag and self.HEREDOC_TAG_IS_IDENTIFIER and (self._end or not tag.isidentifier()):
1332                    if not self._end:
1333                        self._advance(-1)
1334
1335                    self._advance(-len(tag))
1336                    self._add(self.HEREDOC_STRING_ALTERNATIVE)
1337                    return True
1338
1339                end = f"{start}{tag}{end}"
1340        else:
1341            return False
1342
1343        self._advance(len(start))
1344        text = self._extract_string(end, raw_string=token_type == TokenType.RAW_STRING)
1345
1346        if base:
1347            try:
1348                int(text, base)
1349            except Exception:
1350                raise TokenError(
1351                    f"Numeric string contains invalid characters from {self._line}:{self._start}"
1352                )
1353
1354        self._add(token_type, text)
1355        return True
1356
1357    def _scan_identifier(self, identifier_end: str) -> None:
1358        self._advance()
1359        text = self._extract_string(identifier_end, escapes=self._IDENTIFIER_ESCAPES)
1360        self._add(TokenType.IDENTIFIER, text)
1361
1362    def _scan_var(self) -> None:
1363        while True:
1364            char = self._peek.strip()
1365            if char and (char in self.VAR_SINGLE_TOKENS or char not in self.SINGLE_TOKENS):
1366                self._advance(alnum=True)
1367            else:
1368                break
1369
1370        self._add(
1371            TokenType.VAR
1372            if self.tokens and self.tokens[-1].token_type == TokenType.PARAMETER
1373            else self.KEYWORDS.get(self._text.upper(), TokenType.VAR)
1374        )

1376    def _extract_string(
1377        self,
1378        delimiter: str,
1379        escapes: t.Optional[t.Set[str]] = None,
1380        raw_string: bool = False,
1381        raise_unmatched: bool = True,
1382    ) -> str:
1383        text = ""
1384        delim_size = len(delimiter)
1385        escapes = self._STRING_ESCAPES if escapes is None else escapes
1386
1387        while True:
1388            if (
1389                not raw_string
1390                and self.dialect.UNESCAPED_SEQUENCES
1391                and self._peek
1392                and self._char in self.STRING_ESCAPES
1393            ):
1394                unescaped_sequence = self.dialect.UNESCAPED_SEQUENCES.get(self._char + self._peek)
1395                if unescaped_sequence:
1396                    self._advance(2)
1397                    text += unescaped_sequence
1398                    continue
1399            if (
1400                (self.STRING_ESCAPES_ALLOWED_IN_RAW_STRINGS or not raw_string)
1401                and self._char in escapes
1402                and (self._peek == delimiter or self._peek in escapes)
1403                and (self._char not in self._QUOTES or self._char == self._peek)
1404            ):
1405                if self._peek == delimiter:
1406                    text += self._peek
1407                else:
1408                    text += self._char + self._peek
1409
1410                if self._current + 1 < self.size:
1411                    self._advance(2)
1412                else:
1413                    raise TokenError(f"Missing {delimiter} from {self._line}:{self._current}")
1414            else:
1415                if self._chars(delim_size) == delimiter:
1416                    if delim_size > 1:
1417                        self._advance(delim_size - 1)
1418                    break
1419
1420                if self._end:
1421                    if not raise_unmatched:
1422                        return text + self._char
1423
1424                    raise TokenError(f"Missing {delimiter} from {self._line}:{self._start}")
1425
1426                current = self._current - 1
1427                self._advance(alnum=True)
1428                text += self.sql[current : self._current - 1]
1429
1430        return text

1432    def tokenize_rs(self, sql: str) -> t.List[Token]:
1433        if not self._RS_TOKENIZER:
1434            raise SqlglotError("Rust tokenizer is not available")
1435
1436        try:
1437            tokens = self._RS_TOKENIZER.tokenize(sql, self._rs_dialect_settings)
1438            for token in tokens:
1439                token.token_type = _ALL_TOKEN_TYPES[token.token_type_index]
1440            return tokens
1441        except Exception as e:
1442            raise TokenError(str(e))
